Ryan walks us through the skill and knowledge involved in hunting and harvesting a whale, the history of the crews that go back generations, and what this traditional practice means for the life of the community.

If you have a few minutes, check out this spectacular short documentary chronicling spring whaling in Tikiġaq, crafted by Alaska videographer Cale Green and narrated by Ryan Rock, a member of a whaling crew in this far northwest corner of Alaska. https://vimeo.com/375039230

Though not providing a presumption of benefits, our bill would formally recognize a veteran’s exposure to #burnpits during their service in Iraq, Afghanistan and other locations, potentially aiding 1000s pursuing #VA treatment for their related illnesses and health conditions.

It is simply unreasonable for a veteran to have to prove they were exposed to specific toxins from specific #burnpits on specific days in order to receive #VA health care or benefits, which is the burden they face today.  http://sen.gov/9JX6  #veterans

Today @Sen_JoeManchin & I introduced the 𝙑𝙚𝙩𝙚𝙧𝙖𝙣𝙨 𝘽𝙪𝙧𝙣 𝙋𝙞𝙩 𝙀𝙭𝙥𝙤𝙨𝙪𝙧𝙚 𝙍𝙚𝙘𝙤𝙜𝙣𝙞𝙩𝙞𝙤𝙣 𝘼𝙘𝙩 to address a barrier preventing many vets from getting #VA benefits for illnesses and diseases related to their exposure to #burnpits.

Having worked closely w/ advocates & survivors in Alaska, I know how important the Violence Against Women Act is to their work and to the protection of women. Glad to introduce a 10-year #VAWA reauthorization bill earlier today.  https://sen.gov/596N  #EndDV pic.twitter.com/U5qoOolSJo

This #VAWA reauthorization would robustly fund programs to support victims of #DV & sexual assault. @SenJoniErnst's bill deserves the support of every member of the Senate and is an opportunity for Ds & Rs to deliver a major bipartisan achievement that Americans can be proud of.

The statistics are horrifying. They show that our state and country are unquestionably in the midst of a national crisis. This afternoon, I joined @SenJoniErnst in introducing a ten-year reauthorization of the Violence Against Women Act. #VAWA #EndDV
👉  https://sen.gov/596N  pic.twitter.com/5sdllORRzk

Speaking momentarily on the reauthorization of the Violence Against Women Act. I’m grateful to @SenJoniErnst for her work on this package that deserves the support of all 100 Senators. Watch live:  http://Senate.gov/floor  #VAWA

In total, we’ve secured about $1.4 billion in military construction investments for Alaska. This is due, in large part, to the hard work of Alaskans making the case to senior DoD officials, as well as the overall recognition of Alaska’s strategic importance to the #Arctic region.

From maintaining 4/25 at JBER, bringing up the F35s, new ships & infrastructure for @USCG, exploring deep water port near Nome, to conducting a massive military exercise on Adak—Alaska is at the forefront of the Trump administration’s effort to rebuild the military. #Arctic

We are witnessing the beginning of an American awakening to the strategic importance of the #Arctic. This weekend, I penned an op-ed in @adndotcom detailing some of the big developments we’ve achieved in this region working together. 
📰 👉  https://sen.gov/QX9J

Read through the citation to learn more about this tenacious American hero. #Marines pic.twitter.com/kUkYqstNlA
